1
00:00:48,970 --> 00:00:52,330
[Jirisan]

2
00:00:52,330 --> 00:00:57,260
[The places, people, organizations, accidents, and the background stories depicted in this drama are fictional]

3
00:00:57,260 --> 00:01:01,135
Especially not the Black Bridge Valley area. Don't ever go there.

4
00:01:01,135 --> 00:01:02,987
Black Bridge Valley Village.

5
00:01:02,987 --> 00:01:07,799
Have you forgotten all that's happened there?

6
00:01:07,799 --> 00:01:11,912
This place is perfect for cable cars.

7
00:01:11,912 --> 00:01:14,573
We have no intention of moving out. Get out of here.

8
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:16,208
You'll absoutely regret this.

9
00:01:16,208 --> 00:01:17,626
It's him! The cable car man.

10
00:01:17,626 --> 00:01:21,113
He messed with the well to kick us out from here!

11
00:01:21,113 --> 00:01:23,582
Most villagers have left.

12
00:01:23,582 --> 00:01:25,976
I'm not leaving!

13
00:01:28,379 --> 00:01:31,040
It's all because of him.

14
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:34,460
If he hadn't ruined the well...

15
00:01:38,815 --> 00:01:41,667
The deceased was holding this.

16
00:01:41,667 --> 00:01:43,302
Is it really you who did that, Commander?

17
00:01:43,302 --> 00:01:45,295
Is it you who harmed all the other people, too?

18
00:01:45,295 --> 00:01:49,473
Tell Yi Kang at Haedong Ranger Station that I didn't leave the mark this time.

19
00:01:49,473 --> 00:01:53,671
He said he didn't leave the mark this time?

20
00:01:53,671 --> 00:01:56,165
If it wasn't Hyun Jo,

21
00:01:56,165 --> 00:02:00,250
who and why would someone leave a mark?

22
00:02:20,690 --> 00:02:22,733
Senior Yi Kang!

23
00:02:40,110 --> 00:02:43,040
Can you hear me?

24
00:02:57,769 --> 00:03:00,420
Senior Yi Kang!

25
00:03:05,026 --> 00:03:07,219
Can you hear me?

26
00:03:32,195 --> 00:03:33,963
Are you all right?

27
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:38,701
Are you okay?

28
00:03:42,022 --> 00:03:44,523
Why are you here like this?

29
00:04:22,103 --> 00:04:25,331
Why did you try to go up there in such a state?

30
00:04:26,941 --> 00:04:31,153
I heard the commander got arrested.

31
00:04:32,447 --> 00:04:35,908
I also heard a cell phone and gloves were found.

32
00:04:37,535 --> 00:04:40,246
How were they found?

33
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:52,149
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

34
00:04:53,343 --> 00:04:55,386
But Senior.

35
00:04:56,012 --> 00:05:00,558
Anyone could take the gloves if they wanted to.

36
00:05:01,684 --> 00:05:06,004
Don't people wash the gloves at the ranger station with other uniforms?

37
00:05:06,004 --> 00:05:11,001
If one is a national park ranger, taking gloves is a piece of cake.

38
00:05:12,946 --> 00:05:15,364
I'm just saying.

39
00:05:15,364 --> 00:05:17,383
See you then.

40
00:05:26,210 --> 00:05:31,800
[Damseong Police Station]

41
00:05:32,924 --> 00:05:38,884
The investigation is still ongoing, but he's denying all allegations.

42
00:05:41,182 --> 00:05:44,142
Detectives are looking into relevant facts.

43
00:05:44,142 --> 00:05:46,970
But I think he'll be released soon.

44
00:05:58,350 --> 00:06:03,270
[Visiting Room]

45
00:06:25,643 --> 00:06:28,437
I came to ask you something.

46
00:06:32,859 --> 00:06:35,420
On the day that Da Won died...

47
00:06:37,755 --> 00:06:40,783
why did you go to Jeonmuk Valley?

48
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:47,045
Do you still suspect me for this?

49
00:06:47,045 --> 00:06:49,040
I only...

50
00:06:50,143 --> 00:06:53,988
want to know what happened on that day.

51
00:06:56,357 --> 00:07:02,201
I don't know what happened to Da Won that day, either.

52
00:07:03,723 --> 00:07:07,570
If I'd brought her down with me on that day,

53
00:07:08,344 --> 00:07:11,955
she would still be alive.

54
00:07:11,955 --> 00:07:14,108
That's all I can think of.

55
00:07:17,612 --> 00:07:20,489
I saw blood-stained yellow ribbons.

56
00:07:23,718 --> 00:07:27,300
Why were they in your desk drawer?

57
00:07:33,419 --> 00:07:39,756
The ribbons that mislead the hikers and the poisoned yogurts...

58
00:07:41,402 --> 00:07:43,729
You knew about them.

59
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,726
Is that why you came back?

60
00:07:49,994 --> 00:07:52,788
How did you know that?

61
00:07:52,788 --> 00:07:55,357
Visiting time's almost up.

62
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:02,172
Go and see Il Hae.

63
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:05,793
I told him everything I know.

64
00:08:34,172 --> 00:08:36,810
Hello?

65
00:08:36,810 --> 00:08:43,260
[Segyeong Central Hospital]

66
00:08:54,125 --> 00:08:58,718
He's been able to breathe by himself even though he was unconscious.

67
00:08:58,718 --> 00:09:03,759
But since the seizure, he's unable to breathe on his own.

68
00:09:03,759 --> 00:09:10,070
If he continues in this state, he might be determined brain dead.

69
00:09:10,070 --> 00:09:14,186
His family knows about the situation.

70
00:09:14,186 --> 00:09:18,215
I think they'll make a decision soon.

71
00:09:21,486 --> 00:09:23,396
Before that...

72
00:09:26,157 --> 00:09:29,760
If the time comes to let Hyun Jo go...

73
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:34,060
♫ You're everywhere, everywhere ♫

74
00:09:34,060 --> 00:09:36,460
♫ Where my breath reaches ♫

75
00:09:36,460 --> 00:09:39,220
...please let me know in advance. Please.

76
00:09:39,220 --> 00:09:43,240
♫ You can't see me. Even in the forest of memories ♫

77
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:45,100
Yes, I will.

78
00:09:45,100 --> 00:09:47,730
♫ You breathe ♫

79
00:09:47,730 --> 00:09:52,100
♫ Following the long day and night ♫

80
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,780
♫ if I walk and walk again ♫

81
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:56,561
You must be unable to leave the mountain

82
00:09:56,561 --> 00:09:59,932
because of your desire to catch the murderer

83
00:10:04,789 --> 00:10:09,675
What if... What if I catch the murderer,

84
00:10:09,675 --> 00:10:12,390
will you be able to wake up?

85
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:22,270
♫ Between the gaps of time, I'm broken,
I'm breaking like a dying star ♫

86
00:10:22,271 --> 00:10:27,517
This mountain listens to people's desperate prayers,

87
00:10:27,526 --> 00:10:33,049
Perhaps it'll hear my prayer of wanting to save you.

88
00:10:35,409 --> 00:10:39,012
Another death on Jirisan has been reported.

89
00:10:39,013 --> 00:10:42,015
The police have found signs of homicide on this case,

90
00:10:42,016 --> 00:10:46,028
and they're investigating the main suspect under arrest.

91
00:10:53,928 --> 00:10:56,296
We need to talk.

92
00:10:56,296 --> 00:10:59,149
Whatever it's about, let's talk later.

93
00:11:04,897 --> 00:11:08,848
We must talk now. It's important.

94
00:11:08,848 --> 00:11:12,613
Didn't you run off to the headquarters complaining about your leg?

95
00:11:12,613 --> 00:11:15,558
Did you come with Yi Kang?

96
00:11:15,558 --> 00:11:18,496
You suspect the commander, too?

97
00:11:18,496 --> 00:11:22,264
No. Not the commander.

98
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:27,561
You asked why I came back.

99
00:11:30,740 --> 00:11:34,860
Someone's been killing people on the mountains, disguised as accidents.

100
00:11:36,954 --> 00:11:42,283
I came to find out who that was.

101
00:11:42,283 --> 00:11:44,420
What are you talking about?

102
00:11:44,420 --> 00:11:48,482
The commander was thinking the same as Yi Kang.

103
00:11:48,482 --> 00:11:52,044
That someone's been killing people on the mountain.

104
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:01,495
He got lost in Yiseokjae,

105
00:12:01,495 --> 00:12:06,167
but his body was found in completely opposite direction, near Gaeam Falls.

106
00:12:06,167 --> 00:12:07,793
That's right.

107
00:12:07,793 --> 00:12:10,363
The commander found it fishy,

108
00:12:10,363 --> 00:12:13,983
and looked around the area where the victim was found.

109
00:12:15,384 --> 00:12:20,823
Then he found strange ribbons near the valley above Gaeam Falls.

110
00:12:42,646 --> 00:12:46,565
Ribbons? What ribbons?

111
00:12:46,565 --> 00:12:50,211
Like the ones illegal hikers use?

112
00:12:50,211 --> 00:12:52,104
Yeah.

113
00:12:53,047 --> 00:12:55,632
But not just there.

114
00:12:55,632 --> 00:12:59,095
This is a missing person case was from this February, in Oerae Valley.

115
00:12:59,095 --> 00:13:04,266
This person was also found near Bongjaeam, in the opposite direction from where he got lost.

116
00:13:04,266 --> 00:13:07,478
The commander patrolled the area just in case

117
00:13:07,478 --> 00:13:09,997
and found another set of ribbons.

118
00:13:26,555 --> 00:13:30,751
Above Gaeam Falls and Bongjaeam are dangerous places that illegal hikers rarely visit.

119
00:13:30,751 --> 00:13:33,354
But why were the ribbons found there?

120
00:13:34,505 --> 00:13:37,399
Someone led them there to get lost.

121
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:49,250
Not the usual path, but in another way.

122
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:54,126
He lured people to a more treacherous path where people could more easily get into an accident.

123
00:13:54,126 --> 00:13:58,186
And... it's not just the ribbons.

124
00:14:15,463 --> 00:14:18,757
Please give this to Seo Yi Kang.

125
00:14:18,757 --> 00:14:23,027
You don't have to do this. We're only doing our job.

126
00:14:23,028 --> 00:14:25,431
But thank you.

127
00:14:25,431 --> 00:14:27,600
She saved my life.

128
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:32,145
Hwang told me that someone left a yogurt drink in Jeonmuk Valley, too.

129
00:14:32,145 --> 00:14:33,933
Excuse me?

130
00:14:33,933 --> 00:14:38,194
I mean. He didn't go to collect herbs or anything...

131
00:14:38,194 --> 00:14:40,029
A yogurt?

132
00:14:40,029 --> 00:14:44,216
Remember? I also drank one left behind by someone and almost died?

133
00:15:02,092 --> 00:15:05,020
The commander went to Jeonmuk Valley that day

134
00:15:05,020 --> 00:15:06,947
to look for this.

135
00:15:15,731 --> 00:15:19,068
He came to see me with it,

136
00:15:19,068 --> 00:15:24,089
asking for an ingredient check at the headquarters.

137
00:15:26,325 --> 00:15:29,803
So what happened? Did you get the result?

138
00:15:33,958 --> 00:15:38,437
It's too old and spoiled to identify the ingredients.

139
00:15:41,006 --> 00:15:44,267
Hang on.

140
00:15:44,276 --> 00:15:47,823
Then it's only the commander's guess.

141
00:15:47,823 --> 00:15:51,240
Right? It could've been a mere coincidence.

142
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:53,618
The ribbons could have been blown away by the wind.

143
00:15:53,619 --> 00:15:56,730
The yogurt could have gone bad.

144
00:15:56,730 --> 00:15:59,532
Hyun Jo knew about this.

145
00:15:59,532 --> 00:16:01,101
What do you mean?

146
00:16:02,361 --> 00:16:06,799
Hyun Jo knew who the murderer was.

147
00:16:10,186 --> 00:16:12,054
And who would that be?

148
00:16:15,601 --> 00:16:22,231
You asked... why we went up the snowy mountain.

149
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:39,190
[2019]

150
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:55,860
[Kang Hyun Jo]

151
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:14,000
The phone has been turned off and you'll be directed to the voicemail...

152
00:17:15,768 --> 00:17:18,412
Kang Hyun Jo, where are you right now?

153
00:17:21,048 --> 00:17:24,099
Kang Hyun Jo!

154
00:17:31,892 --> 00:17:33,911
Even on that day,

155
00:17:33,911 --> 00:17:36,305
Hyun Jo was chasing the criminal alone.

156
00:19:16,860 --> 00:19:18,520
[Kang Hyun Jo]

157
00:20:09,166 --> 00:20:10,667
Are you all right?

158
00:20:16,448 --> 00:20:19,632
Senior, maybe it's the heavy snow,

159
00:20:19,632 --> 00:20:21,552
but there's no radio signal.

160
00:20:21,553 --> 00:20:25,707
I'll go as far as I need to, to find phone signals.

161
00:20:25,707 --> 00:20:27,643
Please wait here for a moment.

162
00:20:36,777 --> 00:20:39,320
On top of the cornice...

163
00:20:41,373 --> 00:20:43,975
someone left a pole on purpose.

164
00:20:46,928 --> 00:20:50,048
Hyun Jo, you know...

165
00:20:54,219 --> 00:20:56,630
Hang in there.

166
00:20:57,631 --> 00:20:59,466
I'll be right back.

167
00:21:15,591 --> 00:21:18,610
He went out to report,

168
00:21:19,278 --> 00:21:21,571
and never came back.

169
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:27,744
Right, I heard that he called the station that morning.

170
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:52,936
Haedong Ranger Station.

171
00:21:54,546 --> 00:21:56,298
Black Bridge...

172
00:21:56,298 --> 00:21:57,858
Senior is hurt.

173
00:21:59,217 --> 00:22:01,219
Hello? Hyun Jo?

174
00:22:01,219 --> 00:22:03,622
I can't hear you. Where are you?

175
00:22:03,622 --> 00:22:05,657
Black Bridge Valley!

176
00:22:07,284 --> 00:22:09,502
Quick!

177
00:22:13,148 --> 00:22:14,466
Seo Yi Kang!

178
00:22:14,466 --> 00:22:17,095
- Hyun Jo.
- Kang Hyun Jo!

179
00:22:17,095 --> 00:22:18,929
- Seo Yi Kang.
- Kang Hyun Jo!

180
00:22:18,929 --> 00:22:21,048
Senior Yi Kang!

181
00:22:23,383 --> 00:22:26,678
- Is that Hyun Jo?
- Hyun Jo!

182
00:22:27,679 --> 00:22:29,097
Hyun Jo!

183
00:22:30,849 --> 00:22:32,050
Hyun Jo.

184
00:22:33,727 --> 00:22:35,628
I can't find his pulse!

185
00:22:37,773 --> 00:22:39,399
No pulse, Sir.

186
00:22:56,958 --> 00:22:59,690
That wasn't just an accident.

187
00:23:01,113 --> 00:23:03,882
We weren't the only ones up on the mountain that day.

188
00:23:21,942 --> 00:23:24,027
Seo Yi Kang!

189
00:23:46,842 --> 00:23:49,970
Do you mean someone tried to kill you two?

190
00:23:51,012 --> 00:23:54,057
Who would that be? Did the police tell you?

191
00:23:54,916 --> 00:23:56,710
You're saying...

192
00:23:56,710 --> 00:23:59,404
there was someone else at the site besides you and Hyun Jo?

193
00:23:59,404 --> 00:24:00,297
Yes.

194
00:24:00,297 --> 00:24:03,408
Someone left a pole on a snow cornice.

195
00:24:03,408 --> 00:24:05,243
That person intentionally led us to get into an accident.

196
00:24:05,243 --> 00:24:10,662
I'm not asking about that. Has the person directly threatened you in any way?

197
00:24:10,662 --> 00:24:14,166
No... But he had blood on his clothes.

198
00:24:14,166 --> 00:24:16,063
I'm sure Hyun Jo got hurt because of him, too.

199
00:24:16,063 --> 00:24:20,083
Did you witness how Mr. Kang Hyun Jo got hurt?

200
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:24,128
No one believed me.

201
00:24:24,129 --> 00:24:26,965
But someone was surely there.

202
00:24:29,159 --> 00:24:31,720
Though I couldn't see the face...

203
00:24:33,263 --> 00:24:34,748
We must find the person.

204
00:24:34,748 --> 00:24:38,309
That way, we can clear the commander's false charges.

205
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:40,102
How can we? We don't know who it was.

206
00:24:40,103 --> 00:24:42,255
There is a way.

207
00:24:42,255 --> 00:24:43,940
What's that?

208
00:24:46,802 --> 00:24:48,653
Black Bridge Valley.

209
00:24:52,833 --> 00:24:57,229
Hyun Jo went there just before the accident.

210
00:24:57,229 --> 00:25:01,320
If we go there, we will find evidence there.

211
00:25:02,542 --> 00:25:04,169
What evidence?

212
00:25:06,613 --> 00:25:08,298
Not sure yet.

213
00:25:11,635 --> 00:25:15,288
But we'll find out when we get there.

214
00:25:15,288 --> 00:25:17,590
Please take me there.

215
00:25:22,646 --> 00:25:24,614
I can't do this alone.

216
00:25:24,614 --> 00:25:27,634
Please. Help me.

217
00:25:42,332 --> 00:25:44,901
One, two, three!

218
00:25:44,901 --> 00:25:47,294
I said we can go by ourselves.

219
00:25:47,295 --> 00:25:50,339
How will you get there without assistance?

220
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:07,460
[4 hours ago]

221
00:26:19,369 --> 00:26:21,354
Jeong Goo Yeong?

222
00:26:21,354 --> 00:26:24,316
No way. Why would he...?

223
00:26:24,316 --> 00:26:26,375
It has to be one of the park rangers.

224
00:26:26,376 --> 00:26:29,796
The murderer was wearing our uniform.

225
00:26:36,036 --> 00:26:39,206
Goo Yeong was on the mountain when Da Won got lost.

226
00:26:39,206 --> 00:26:42,267
He could've easily got the commander's gloves into her hand.

227
00:26:46,588 --> 00:26:49,257
So? What are we going to do?

228
00:26:49,257 --> 00:26:51,484
Take Goo Yeong in?

229
00:26:52,360 --> 00:26:54,945
No. The police won't believe us.

230
00:26:54,946 --> 00:26:56,990
We must take him ourselves.

231
00:26:58,458 --> 00:27:01,253
Once he finds out I have crucial evidence,

232
00:27:01,253 --> 00:27:04,064
he'll try to kill me.

233
00:27:04,064 --> 00:27:06,957
- Let's get the proof then.
- No.

234
00:27:06,958 --> 00:27:08,792
No way.

235
00:27:08,793 --> 00:27:11,379
You could get into danger.

236
00:27:12,464 --> 00:27:13,422
Be careful.

237
00:27:13,423 --> 00:27:14,824
There.

238
00:27:18,703 --> 00:27:20,805
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

239
00:27:27,754 --> 00:27:29,272
By the way...

240
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:34,950
Why did you go to the mountain that day?

241
00:27:37,889 --> 00:27:40,420
The day Da Won went missing.

242
00:27:41,351 --> 00:27:43,645
Why did you go there?

243
00:27:43,645 --> 00:27:45,363
Da Won?

244
00:27:47,565 --> 00:27:49,200
Is that you?

245
00:28:07,936 --> 00:28:09,929
I had things to do.

246
00:28:11,506 --> 00:28:13,108
Let's get going.

247
00:28:37,324 --> 00:28:40,343
One thing I couldn't tell you guys about...

248
00:28:41,119 --> 00:28:43,104
Hyun Jo.

249
00:28:43,104 --> 00:28:46,691
If I end up dying...

250
00:28:46,691 --> 00:28:49,719
maybe I can meet Hyun Jo.

251
00:28:52,213 --> 00:28:53,757
If I see him,

252
00:28:53,757 --> 00:28:58,978
maybe I could tell him what I couldn't hear, what I couldn't say.

253
00:29:15,295 --> 00:29:17,380
Let's take a break here.

254
00:29:34,964 --> 00:29:36,232
Here.

255
00:29:37,676 --> 00:29:39,569
Oh, thanks.

256
00:29:53,341 --> 00:29:57,587
How long have you and Hyun Jo known about this?

257
00:29:58,405 --> 00:30:02,050
Have you two been investigating on your own the whole time?

258
00:30:06,271 --> 00:30:09,916
That's why you two were always together.

259
00:30:12,961 --> 00:30:15,572
Did Hyun Jo tell you anything

260
00:30:15,572 --> 00:30:18,316
before the accident on the snowy mountain?

261
00:30:22,387 --> 00:30:23,810
No.

262
00:30:24,472 --> 00:30:27,183
After that incident last summer,

263
00:30:27,183 --> 00:30:29,118
I haven't been able to see him.

264
00:30:31,479 --> 00:30:33,122
Last summer...

265
00:30:35,117 --> 00:30:37,780
A lot of painful things happened.

266
00:30:46,070 --> 00:30:52,060
[2019]

267
00:31:00,108 --> 00:31:01,509
Gosh.

268
00:31:02,577 --> 00:31:06,264
Why do we lose every single game?

269
00:31:07,348 --> 00:31:10,268
You shouldn't throw "yut" sticks so hard.

270
00:31:10,268 --> 00:31:12,145
You drop them outside the mat every time.

271
00:31:12,145 --> 00:31:15,664
Hey! We could've easily won if you avoided "geol" there.

272
00:31:15,665 --> 00:31:17,374
Exactly, right, Senior.

273
00:31:17,375 --> 00:31:21,003
You should use your brain more often.

274
00:31:30,146 --> 00:31:34,000
You said you saw black hiking gloves.

275
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:35,627
Yes.

276
00:31:35,627 --> 00:31:40,507
As you're aware, plenty of black hiking gloves are strewn all over Jirisan

277
00:31:40,507 --> 00:31:41,991
And I don't mean just rangers.

278
00:31:41,991 --> 00:31:46,154
If you include the hikers and the residents, you can't even count them.

279
00:31:47,580 --> 00:31:51,400
We can't tell the murderer just by the gloves.

280
00:31:51,976 --> 00:31:54,479
It has to do with the mountain.

281
00:31:54,479 --> 00:31:58,733
All the victims had something to do with the mountain.

282
00:31:58,733 --> 00:32:01,544
Poachers, herb collectors,

283
00:32:02,487 --> 00:32:04,570
Hyeon Su, who died during the march,

284
00:32:05,782 --> 00:32:08,426
also said that this is his hometown.

285
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:13,890
But...

286
00:32:13,890 --> 00:32:18,486
there are a decent number of people who have lived near Jirisan for generations.

287
00:32:18,486 --> 00:32:20,763
It could just be a coincidence, too.

288
00:32:23,900 --> 00:32:25,926
But why exactly?

289
00:32:26,536 --> 00:32:28,640
Why is the murderer

290
00:32:29,430 --> 00:32:32,325
killing people on this mountain?

291
00:32:33,793 --> 00:32:35,912
One thing I'm sure of.

292
00:32:36,771 --> 00:32:38,957
It's a totally crazy person.

293
00:32:50,310 --> 00:32:52,011
You know what though?

294
00:32:53,062 --> 00:32:54,981
What?

295
00:32:54,981 --> 00:32:58,893
Today's our one-year anniversary.

296
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:03,740
What?

297
00:33:03,740 --> 00:33:07,927
Are we dating? Why would you keep track of that?

298
00:33:07,927 --> 00:33:10,346
I didn't say that.

299
00:33:10,346 --> 00:33:14,158
I just meant it's been a year since the day we saved Seung Hoon.

300
00:33:18,621 --> 00:33:19,981
So what?

301
00:33:19,981 --> 00:33:22,583
Should I light a candle on a cake for you?

302
00:33:24,627 --> 00:33:26,087
Seriously.

303
00:33:28,264 --> 00:33:30,141
Jeez.

304
00:33:30,141 --> 00:33:33,102
Hey, go run the errands by yourself.

305
00:33:33,102 --> 00:33:34,344
Huh? But we lost together.

306
00:33:34,345 --> 00:33:36,097
I'm busy!

307
00:33:48,651 --> 00:33:50,653
Look who it is!

308
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:54,015
"Yut" game loser Hyun Jo!

309
00:33:54,015 --> 00:33:57,293
- Hurry over here.
- Hurry up!

310
00:34:09,614 --> 00:34:12,340
Ugh, this is warm.

311
00:34:12,341 --> 00:34:15,719
It took four hours to get here.

312
00:34:15,720 --> 00:34:17,355
Two hundred and forty minutes.

313
00:34:17,355 --> 00:34:21,484
Back in my days, we carried an icebox with drinks on our heads.

314
00:34:21,484 --> 00:34:24,312
- Filled to the brim with ice.
- I'm leaving.

315
00:34:26,906 --> 00:34:28,191
Hey!

316
00:34:28,967 --> 00:34:31,135
That's my drumstick!

317
00:34:32,537 --> 00:34:34,138
Hey!

318
00:34:34,138 --> 00:34:35,615
That's not yours.

319
00:34:36,432 --> 00:34:37,767
This one's spicy.

320
00:34:37,767 --> 00:34:39,519
How dare you take the crispy one.

321
00:34:39,519 --> 00:34:41,553
Really?

322
00:34:49,921 --> 00:34:51,622
Ready to go?

323
00:34:57,428 --> 00:35:00,940
The "yut" game loser Seo Yi Kang.

324
00:35:00,940 --> 00:35:03,142
We will get off first.

325
00:35:04,852 --> 00:35:07,438
See you tomorrow.

326
00:35:17,373 --> 00:35:19,825
Hello? Hello?

327
00:35:19,826 --> 00:35:21,352
What happened?

328
00:35:21,352 --> 00:35:24,313
I saw a man collapse on my way down the mountain.

329
00:35:24,313 --> 00:35:27,415
I shook him, but he didn't wake up and didn't seem to be breathing either.

330
00:35:27,416 --> 00:35:29,677
I was too scared and my battery ran out.

331
00:35:29,677 --> 00:35:32,030
- So I just ran...
- Where did you see him?

332
00:35:32,030 --> 00:35:33,922
Well, umm...

333
00:35:33,923 --> 00:35:36,384
Where was it? Over there, somewhere.

334
00:35:45,376 --> 00:35:50,227
Haedong One. An injured man reported at 2.5 km on the trail, near Seon Rock.

335
00:35:50,227 --> 00:35:53,316
Kang Hyun Jo speaking. I'm 2 km away from Seonbawi Rock.

336
00:35:53,317 --> 00:35:54,844
I'll go there.

337
00:35:54,844 --> 00:35:56,079
I'll leave now, too.

338
00:35:56,079 --> 00:35:59,732
It seemed like he was unable to breathe. Hurry up.

339
00:36:45,294 --> 00:36:46,746
Are you all right?

340
00:36:48,873 --> 00:36:51,918
Have you called the police?

341
00:36:56,781 --> 00:36:59,909
I'll keep watch till the police arrive. You go down first.

342
00:36:59,909 --> 00:37:02,762
It's fine. I'm a ranger, too.

343
00:37:40,032 --> 00:37:41,509
Do you remember...

344
00:37:43,286 --> 00:37:48,099
I told you about my colleague who died on the mountain?

345
00:37:50,100 --> 00:37:56,500
Well... His military dog tags were never found.

346
00:37:57,525 --> 00:37:59,860
That kept bothering me,

347
00:38:02,613 --> 00:38:05,616
so I came here to look for them.

348
00:38:18,112 --> 00:38:20,447
This mountain frightened me

349
00:38:20,447 --> 00:38:23,491
since Hyeon Su died.

350
00:38:27,021 --> 00:38:31,438
But... I wanted to find my junior's article

351
00:38:32,710 --> 00:38:35,362
and return it to his family.

352
00:38:37,156 --> 00:38:39,399
I walked with my head down,

353
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:41,736
because I didn't want to see anything else.

354
00:38:45,431 --> 00:38:48,100
I only thought about finding the dog tags and coming back.

355
00:38:48,100 --> 00:38:50,286
That was the only thing on my mind.

356
00:39:01,697 --> 00:39:03,770
But on that day...

357
00:39:04,575 --> 00:39:08,179
the mountain looked so beautiful.

358
00:39:09,163 --> 00:39:12,410
The mountain I saw that day wasn't an object of fear.

359
00:39:19,323 --> 00:39:22,851
I don't know why he came here today.

360
00:39:23,636 --> 00:39:30,579
But... I hope he got comforted by the mountain as I was.

361
00:40:00,314 --> 00:40:03,317
These flowers represent happiness.

362
00:40:28,310 --> 00:40:30,760
[Summer Disaster 2019]

363
00:40:42,906 --> 00:40:44,450
Mr. Needle.

364
00:40:45,401 --> 00:40:46,577
Are you looking for Ms. Thread?

365
00:40:46,577 --> 00:40:50,522
I think you're the needle and the thread.

366
00:40:54,251 --> 00:40:56,428
- Should we sit here?
- Yeah.

367
00:40:59,882 --> 00:41:03,510
You haven't had breakfast, right? Here, try this. It's really good.

368
00:41:04,295 --> 00:41:07,031
- Thank you.
- The coffee's hot.

369
00:41:07,031 --> 00:41:09,425
I also haven't had breakfast yet.

370
00:41:10,284 --> 00:41:12,728
It's almost lunchtime. You should wait.

371
00:41:14,146 --> 00:41:15,681
Is it good?

372
00:41:19,476 --> 00:41:21,428
Let me know if you want more.

373
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:31,697
Yi Kang took a day off today.

374
00:41:32,890 --> 00:41:35,326
It's not going to be good news anyway.

375
00:41:38,637 --> 00:41:40,022
Is everyone here?

376
00:41:40,022 --> 00:41:41,957
- Hello, Sir.
- Sit, sit.

377
00:41:46,112 --> 00:41:48,681
I'll go ahead since everyone's here.

378
00:41:48,681 --> 00:41:53,244
The most representative summer disaster is a torrential downpour.

379
00:41:53,244 --> 00:41:56,355
There's a saying, "Clouds hang on the mountain ridge."

380
00:41:56,355 --> 00:41:59,708
When rainclouds can't pass over huge mountains over a thousand meters tall,

381
00:41:59,708 --> 00:42:02,294
local torrential rainfall can occur,

382
00:42:02,294 --> 00:42:07,091
which is unpredictable by the weather forecast and is therefore very dangerous.

383
00:42:07,091 --> 00:42:09,243
Such local torrential rainfall is also dangerous

384
00:42:09,243 --> 00:42:13,180
because it could pour on the top of the mountain but clear below,

385
00:42:13,180 --> 00:42:16,809
so it's hard to estimate the danger.

386
00:42:16,809 --> 00:42:18,502
The rougher the geographical features,

387
00:42:18,502 --> 00:42:22,089
the more water it'll collect, increasing the flow ever so fast.

388
00:42:22,089 --> 00:42:25,818
At its most rapid, it'll engulf downstream with more than three meters per second,

389
00:42:25,818 --> 00:42:29,805
which is strong enough to uproot trees and wipe buildings away.

390
00:42:29,805 --> 00:42:32,208
Like the expression, "Water comes standing,"

391
00:42:32,208 --> 00:42:36,395
it might be too late for you to run by the time you detect danger.

392
00:42:36,395 --> 00:42:41,984
A good example would be the Dowon Valley flood in 1995.

393
00:42:41,984 --> 00:42:45,738
Over 200 mm of torrential downpour occurred then,

394
00:42:45,738 --> 00:42:47,406
sweeping everything in the valley

395
00:42:47,406 --> 00:42:51,160
in less than an hour.

396
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:54,163
We were helpless in the past,

397
00:42:54,163 --> 00:42:56,515
but not as much now.

398
00:42:56,515 --> 00:42:58,334
Thanks to the response systems

399
00:42:58,334 --> 00:43:01,437
such as AWS and the automatic rain gauge,

400
00:43:01,437 --> 00:43:04,865
casualties are less than before.

401
00:43:05,483 --> 00:43:08,427
But we still need to be vigilant.

402
00:43:08,427 --> 00:43:11,504
Take special caution on preventing flood-related accidents

403
00:43:11,505 --> 00:43:14,283
by fortifying patrols during the disaster prevention period

404
00:43:14,283 --> 00:43:16,118
for illegal camping and cooking

405
00:43:16,118 --> 00:43:18,136
in the national park and on campsites

406
00:43:18,137 --> 00:43:22,307
near valleys vulnerable to flooding.

407
00:43:22,308 --> 00:43:23,934
Yes, Sir!

408
00:43:37,123 --> 00:43:40,450
Put those in the cabinet.

409
00:43:40,451 --> 00:43:42,169
You know it's the village ancestral rites today, right?

410
00:43:42,169 --> 00:43:44,997
Come to the town hall and help.

411
00:43:47,374 --> 00:43:49,208
Well...

412
00:43:49,209 --> 00:43:51,669
Yi Kang's parents...

413
00:43:51,670 --> 00:43:54,173
How did they pass away?

414
00:43:57,743 --> 00:43:59,995
The shelter they were in

415
00:43:59,995 --> 00:44:02,548
got swept away by a valley flood.

416
00:44:04,141 --> 00:44:07,278
I understand why Yi Kang doesn't want to come to the ritual.

417
00:44:07,278 --> 00:44:08,779
Pardon?

418
00:44:08,779 --> 00:44:13,433
There are records from before the building got swept away.

419
00:44:14,201 --> 00:44:15,861
Records?

420
00:44:16,595 --> 00:44:17,696
Yeah.

421
00:44:18,806 --> 00:44:22,418
There's a notebook with people's conversations from that day.

422
00:44:22,418 --> 00:44:26,997
They put it in a safe just in case, and it got found later.

423
00:44:27,815 --> 00:44:29,717
Everyone there

424
00:44:29,717 --> 00:44:32,528
left a will to their family,

425
00:44:32,528 --> 00:44:36,599
but only Yi Kang's parents didn't leave a single word.

426
00:44:36,599 --> 00:44:39,802
She's probably had a hard time because of it.

427
00:44:49,640 --> 00:44:54,390
[We're closing early due to personal circumstances.]

428
00:44:56,819 --> 00:44:57,610
Hey, Yi Kang.

429
00:44:57,611 --> 00:45:00,196
Where are you going again?

430
00:45:00,197 --> 00:45:02,990
I told you, not today.

431
00:45:02,991 --> 00:45:05,785
We're in charge of the ritual service food today.

432
00:45:05,786 --> 00:45:07,954
Do you want me to cook everything alone?

433
00:45:07,955 --> 00:45:11,207
You're not alone. You got plenty of helpers around.

434
00:45:11,208 --> 00:45:13,209
What are you saying? Listen, girl!

435
00:45:13,210 --> 00:45:15,294
If it's that hard, don't do it.

436
00:45:15,295 --> 00:45:18,464
Stop right there!

437
00:45:18,465 --> 00:45:22,176
When will you stop being like this?

438
00:45:22,177 --> 00:45:25,789
Are you not going to prepare me a ritual table when I die?

439
00:45:25,789 --> 00:45:28,083
Please stop saying that.

440
00:45:28,083 --> 00:45:29,585
What are you saying?

441
00:45:29,585 --> 00:45:30,819
Hey!

442
00:45:30,819 --> 00:45:32,603
Oh, that girl.

443
00:45:32,604 --> 00:45:35,407
What will I do with her?

444
00:45:35,407 --> 00:45:37,818
That's girls is such a pain in the neck!

445
00:45:57,579 --> 00:45:59,405
- You must be from the national park.
- Yes, we are.

446
00:45:59,405 --> 00:46:01,666
Thank you for coming out.

447
00:46:02,685 --> 00:46:05,812
- Eleven in total, right?
- Yes.

448
00:46:06,455 --> 00:46:10,109
We'll be climbing 7 km to Deokseoryeong as you requested.

449
00:46:10,109 --> 00:46:12,544
Today, we'll spend the night at Bidam Shelter

450
00:46:12,544 --> 00:46:14,363
and climb the rest tomorrow.

451
00:46:14,363 --> 00:46:16,240
Yes. Very good.

452
00:46:16,240 --> 00:46:19,034
What about the environmental organization who are coming with us?

453
00:46:19,034 --> 00:46:20,928
Here we are.

454
00:46:20,928 --> 00:46:22,746
Hello, Sir.

455
00:46:22,746 --> 00:46:24,698
Five, right?

456
00:46:26,241 --> 00:46:29,645
We trust that you packed everything you would need.

457
00:46:29,645 --> 00:46:31,630
Then, let's roll.

458
00:46:31,630 --> 00:46:33,573
How have you been, Sir?

459
00:46:39,597 --> 00:46:41,248
Yes, why?

460
00:46:42,933 --> 00:46:44,885
Where else? I'm on the mountain.

461
00:46:46,879 --> 00:46:49,606
Because of the lottery ticket, duh.

462
00:46:49,606 --> 00:46:53,084
Okay. I'll call you when I get back down.

463
00:47:41,860 --> 00:47:45,350
The call cannot be connected. You'll be directed to the voicemail...

464
00:47:45,350 --> 00:47:47,430
After the beep...

465
00:47:56,690 --> 00:47:59,376
Why are you so late?

466
00:48:00,328 --> 00:48:03,171
Is Yi Kang here?

467
00:48:04,139 --> 00:48:05,974
Do you even listen to me?

468
00:48:05,974 --> 00:48:08,676
I told you she's not coming. Why would you look for her here?

469
00:48:08,677 --> 00:48:09,978
Hey!

470
00:48:09,978 --> 00:48:12,689
Why are you slacking off?

471
00:48:12,689 --> 00:48:15,349
What? I've been working so hard till now.

472
00:48:15,350 --> 00:48:19,671
Yeah, yeah. Go put these on the tables.

473
00:48:20,464 --> 00:48:23,233
- Hyun Jo, please help him.
- Yes.

474
00:48:24,109 --> 00:48:25,244
You...

475
00:48:25,244 --> 00:48:27,604
I did all of this.

476
00:48:50,710 --> 00:48:54,000
[Haedong Village Volunteer Rescue Team - May, 1995]

477
00:49:01,588 --> 00:49:03,440
Choi Il Man.

478
00:49:05,830 --> 00:49:08,170
[Choi Il Man, October 15, 2018]
[Death due to a potato bomb explosion at the burial site in Saema Valley]

479
00:49:09,471 --> 00:49:10,571
Kim Jin Deok.

480
00:49:10,630 --> 00:49:12,240
[Kim Jin Deok, March 23, 2018]
[Death due to a fall at the Nari Valley in Mihyungri]

481
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:13,283
Lee Jong Goo.

482
00:49:13,360 --> 00:49:15,250
[Lee Jong-g Goo, January 20, 2018]
[Death due to a fall at Booam Cliff at Deokseoryeong]

483
00:49:20,457 --> 00:49:23,043
Why are they all together?

484
00:49:23,735 --> 00:49:25,879
What are you doing? Get to work.

485
00:49:29,007 --> 00:49:30,133
Goo Yeong.

486
00:49:31,535 --> 00:49:35,329
- You said there were records of the 1995 flooding.
- Yup.

487
00:49:35,329 --> 00:49:37,665
Where are they now?

488
00:49:37,665 --> 00:49:40,677
In the document room at the main station. Why?

489
00:49:41,987 --> 00:49:43,572
Hey!

490
00:49:43,572 --> 00:49:45,700
Let's get some work done.

491
00:49:45,700 --> 00:49:48,720
[Document Room | Authorized Personnel Only]

492
00:49:51,013 --> 00:49:52,863
You can look for it on this shelf.

493
00:49:52,864 --> 00:49:54,366
Thank you.

