506
00:50:51,720 --> 00:50:56,269
8:45 a.m. Showers continued and water in the valley started to rise.

507
00:50:56,269 --> 00:50:59,850
1:15 p.m. Damage on deck detected.

508
00:50:59,900 --> 00:51:03,500
A lot of stones and sand from the trail got inside, it was difficult to remove

509
00:51:03,543 --> 00:51:09,306
2:20 p.m. Water in the valley kept rising due to heavy rainfalls.

510
00:51:09,306 --> 00:51:12,730
3:50 p.m. Rainfalls got more severe.

511
00:51:12,730 --> 00:51:16,760
The valley starts to flood. Reported the damage to the main station.

512
00:51:16,764 --> 00:51:20,200
4:50 p.m. Contacted the main station.

513
00:51:20,200 --> 00:51:23,970
But due to the worsening weather, the call got cut off.

514
00:51:23,970 --> 00:51:26,940
No radio signal was available.

515
00:51:31,603 --> 00:51:36,840
5:15 p.m. Five hikers, volunteer fire fighters, and two residents

516
00:51:36,840 --> 00:51:41,203
who got isolated at a nearby campsite escaped to the office.

517
00:51:41,203 --> 00:51:44,525
Hikers, an old man with a fractured leg and his wife.

518
00:51:44,525 --> 00:51:47,246
Three college students in their twenties.

519
00:51:49,380 --> 00:51:54,610
Volunteer fire squad Choi Il Man, Lee Jong Go, Kim Jin Deok.

520
00:51:54,610 --> 00:51:58,239
Residents Seo Yeong Jin, Yoon Soo Mi.

521
00:51:58,240 --> 00:52:01,643
Rangers Jo Dae Jin, Kim Nam Sik.

522
00:52:01,643 --> 00:52:05,670
Decided to wait on the first floor of the office.

523
00:52:12,070 --> 00:52:16,090
7:34 p.m. The bridge collapsed.

524
00:52:19,811 --> 00:52:22,021
What happened?

525
00:52:22,021 --> 00:52:24,882
- Have you contacted the rescue team?
- Yes.

526
00:52:24,882 --> 00:52:28,135
They said they were leaving, so they'll be here soon.

527
00:52:28,135 --> 00:52:30,847
Let's just get out on our own.

528
00:52:30,847 --> 00:52:33,516
- We'll all die if we stay.
- Yes, yes.

529
00:52:33,516 --> 00:52:35,426
Let's just go.

530
00:52:35,426 --> 00:52:36,369
Please wait a little longer.

531
00:52:36,369 --> 00:52:38,746
For how long?

532
00:52:38,746 --> 00:52:41,883
8:00 p.m. No rescue squad yet.

533
00:52:41,883 --> 00:52:46,430
People started discussing the possibility of escaping the office building.

534
00:52:47,622 --> 00:52:50,391
- Jesus.
- Ouch.

535
00:52:51,668 --> 00:52:54,253
- Are you okay?
- Yes, we're good.

536
00:52:54,253 --> 00:52:57,924
See? It's still not late to move out of here.

537
00:52:57,924 --> 00:53:00,026
Wait!

538
00:53:01,903 --> 00:53:03,646
I'm so scared.

539
00:53:07,718 --> 00:53:11,178
I'll cross first and connect the rope.

540
00:53:11,178 --> 00:53:13,389
It's too dangerous. The current's too fast.

541
00:53:13,389 --> 00:53:16,726
I'll try. I'll go down and bring the rescue squad.

542
00:53:16,726 --> 00:53:19,937
- Let me come with you.
- Me, too!

543
00:53:19,937 --> 00:53:21,797
Let's go.

544
00:53:21,797 --> 00:53:24,150
- I'll go, too.
- Let's go.

545
00:53:24,150 --> 00:53:25,843
Let's get out!

546
00:53:29,631 --> 00:53:31,382
I'll stay back.

547
00:53:33,719 --> 00:53:35,302
We'll stay back, too.

548
00:53:35,302 --> 00:53:39,710
If anything happens, you could use some help.

549
00:53:48,275 --> 00:53:50,660
We'll return soon to rescue you all.

550
00:53:59,611 --> 00:54:01,371
Are you all right?

551
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:36,210
9:32 p.m. Two hikers and two residents left the office building.

552
00:54:43,620 --> 00:54:46,260
[Daily Situation Record - August]

553
00:54:46,260 --> 00:54:50,569
9:40 p.m. The water level has exceeded one meter,

554
00:54:50,569 --> 00:54:53,790
and the building has tilted more to the left.

555
00:54:55,175 --> 00:54:57,159
Why are you writing that?

556
00:54:57,159 --> 00:55:00,780
No one will be able to see it anyway.

557
00:55:01,681 --> 00:55:04,166
I'll put it in the safe.

558
00:55:04,166 --> 00:55:09,906
We should let people know what happened here.

559
00:55:09,906 --> 00:55:12,675
Can I write, too?

560
00:55:12,675 --> 00:55:17,055
I want to leave a message to my children.

561
00:55:27,332 --> 00:55:30,793
Won Sik, Won Jae.

562
00:55:30,793 --> 00:55:34,855
Thank you for everything.

563
00:55:34,855 --> 00:55:40,316
Please stay happy and healthy in future.

564
00:56:01,032 --> 00:56:03,743
Would you like to write something?

565
00:56:04,494 --> 00:56:08,064
No, thank you.

566
00:56:20,594 --> 00:56:22,745
And you?

567
00:56:22,745 --> 00:56:26,149
Don't you want to leave a message?

568
00:56:28,310 --> 00:56:32,380
I did leave a message.

569
00:56:34,120 --> 00:56:40,630
[Won Sik, Won Jae. Thank you for everything,]

570
00:56:43,174 --> 00:56:45,117
My dear son, Hyeon Su.

571
00:56:45,117 --> 00:56:47,244
Take good care of your mother.

572
00:56:47,244 --> 00:56:53,525
I hope you will continue to be healthy like now.

573
00:56:53,525 --> 00:56:58,350
Kim Nam Sik, Jirisan National Park Ranger.

574
00:57:04,660 --> 00:57:07,180
[My dear son, Hyeon Su]

575
00:57:07,180 --> 00:57:09,391
Hyeon Su...

576
00:57:09,391 --> 00:57:11,678
Kim Hyeon Su.

577
00:57:12,462 --> 00:57:14,558
Kim Hyeon Su, are you all right?

578
00:57:14,558 --> 00:57:15,959
This is your hometown, right?

579
00:57:15,959 --> 00:57:18,903
- That's right, Sir!
- Must be nice.

580
00:57:18,903 --> 00:57:22,460
I hope your hometown energizes you.

581
00:57:34,501 --> 00:57:37,369
Yes, Captain Kang, what's going on?

582
00:57:37,369 --> 00:57:40,089
I need to check something.

583
00:57:40,089 --> 00:57:45,133
Could you give me the full name of the deceased Private Kim Hyeon Su's father?

584
00:57:45,133 --> 00:57:46,863
Sir?

585
00:57:48,098 --> 00:57:50,975
It's urgent.

586
00:57:50,975 --> 00:57:52,434
Yes. Hold on, please.

587
00:57:52,434 --> 00:57:56,550
I'm in the administration office now, so let me pull that up on my computer.

588
00:58:01,130 --> 00:58:04,970
[My dear son, Hyeon Su]

589
00:58:06,658 --> 00:58:09,910
Captain, I found it.

590
00:58:09,910 --> 00:58:14,554
Private Kim's father's name is Kim Nam Sik.

591
00:58:16,110 --> 00:58:20,740
[Ranger Kim Nam Sik]

592
00:58:25,300 --> 00:58:26,250
[List of Evacuees from the Dowon Valley flood]

593
00:58:26,250 --> 00:58:27,870
[Choi Il Man, Lee Jong Gooo, Kim Jin Deok, Jo Dae Jin]

594
00:58:27,870 --> 00:58:29,100
[List of Casualties from the Dowon Valley flood]

595
00:58:29,100 --> 00:58:29,970
[Seo Young Jin, Yoon Soo Mi, Lee Hyeon Sik, Jang Mi Ja, Kim Nam Sik]

596
00:58:29,970 --> 00:58:33,370
[Kim Nam Sik]

597
00:58:38,450 --> 00:58:43,160
[My dear son, Kim Hyeon Su]

598
00:58:43,160 --> 00:58:46,800
[Kim Nam Sik]

599
00:58:48,867 --> 00:58:51,150
All the victims...

600
00:58:52,078 --> 00:58:57,955
are related to the 1995 flood.

601
00:59:09,804 --> 00:59:12,222
Whar brings you here?

602
00:59:12,222 --> 00:59:14,584
Didn't you go to the ritual?

603
00:59:16,644 --> 00:59:19,970
You know I'm kinda tired of them now.

604
00:59:19,970 --> 00:59:22,475
Tired of them?

605
00:59:22,475 --> 00:59:26,545
Then, why are you here? Did you come to see that?

606
00:59:27,964 --> 00:59:29,974
To get some energy?

607
00:59:31,201 --> 00:59:33,327
Gwigam Rock.

608
00:59:34,079 --> 00:59:36,920
It's surely a powerful rock.

609
00:59:40,502 --> 00:59:43,554
Are you here because of that?

610
00:59:44,923 --> 00:59:46,924
Or...

611
00:59:48,818 --> 00:59:51,404
is there another reason?

612
01:00:07,587 --> 01:00:09,664
That's strange.

613
01:00:14,219 --> 01:00:17,013
Doesn't the air feel heavy?

614
01:00:59,338 --> 01:01:01,556
Please be careful. Let's cross slowly.

615
01:01:01,556 --> 01:01:03,409
Okay.

616
01:02:30,040 --> 01:02:33,350
[Yedong Town Hall]

617
01:03:02,580 --> 01:03:08,700
♫ My little garden ♫

618
01:03:08,700 --> 01:03:14,400
♫ Is always the start of my day ♫

619
01:03:14,400 --> 01:03:23,380
♫ Are there any words it would like to say? ♫

620
01:03:26,240 --> 01:03:28,910
[Jirisan]

621
01:03:28,910 --> 01:03:30,689
Get out of the valley!

622
01:03:30,689 --> 01:03:32,041
Quick! Get out of there!

623
01:03:32,041 --> 01:03:34,850
More localized rain can occur. We must rescue everyone before then.

624
01:03:34,850 --> 01:03:36,212
I'll go.

625
01:03:36,212 --> 01:03:38,330
You must keep watch here, Commander.

626
01:03:38,330 --> 01:03:41,575
Black Bridge Village is gone because of you.

627
01:03:41,575 --> 01:03:45,312
You might not get the benefit if it was suicide.

628
01:03:45,312 --> 01:03:48,732
I think the murderer has something to do with the 1995 flood.

629
01:03:48,732 --> 01:03:50,542
Did something happen back then?

630
01:03:50,542 --> 01:03:53,102
- They just made an unfortunate choice.
- Senior Yi Kang!

631
01:03:53,102 --> 01:03:54,405
Don't lie.

632
01:03:54,405 --> 01:03:56,920
I wanted to forget.

633
01:03:56,920 --> 01:04:02,380
♫ And its words that won't change ♫
